The paper deals with image classification of handwritten digits using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of state-of-the-art algorithm DenseNet and end-to-end training also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of cross-validation and achieving high accuracy, which are common topics in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
